{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3572352,"name":"nfoert","username":"nfoert","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nfoert/{size}/235138_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-29T17:56:46.496Z","cooked":"<p>Hello all! We’re working on fixing our auto alignment code and we’re running into some strange issues where occasionally, when we’re at or near the position already, our code crashes with a <code>Bad optional access</code> error. We’re using C++ and PathPlanner lib <code>2025.2.5</code></p>
<pre data-code-wrap="cpp"><code class="lang-cpp">frc2::CommandPtr DrivetrainSubsystem::GoToPose(Pose2d pose) {
    PathConstraints constraints = PathConstraints(MAX_LINEAR_SPEED, MAX_LINEAR_ACCELERATION, MAX_ROTATION_SPEED, MAX_ROTATION_ACCELERATION);
    std::vector&lt;frc::Pose2d&gt; poses{GetPose(), pose};

    std::vector&lt;Waypoint&gt; waypoints = PathPlannerPath::waypointsFromPoses(poses);

    auto path = std::make_shared&lt;PathPlannerPath&gt;(
        waypoints,
        constraints,
        std::nullopt, // The ideal starting state, this is only relevant for pre-planned paths, so can be nullopt for on-the-fly paths.
        GoalEndState(0.0_mps, pose.Rotation()) // Goal end state. You can set a holonomic rotation here. If using a differential drivetrain, the rotation will have no effect.
    );

    path-&gt;preventFlipping = true;

    _target_position = pose;

    if (pose.Translation().Distance(GetPose().Translation()) &gt; MINIMUM_PATHFIND_DISTANCE) {
        return frc2::cmd::Sequence(
            AutoBuilder::followPath(path), 
            FinalAlignmentCommand{this, pose}.ToPtr(),
            this-&gt;RunOnce([this] {StopMotors();})
        );
    } else {
        return frc2::cmd::Sequence(
            FinalAlignmentCommand{this, pose}.ToPtr(),
            this-&gt;RunOnce([this] {StopMotors();})
        );
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>This is our current function for this functionality. We attempted to fix this by only running the command to go to a path if we’re within 6 inches (<code>MINIMUM_PATHFIND_DISTANCE</code>), however we’re still running into this issue.</p>
<p>The only information put into the logs is <code>Bad optional access</code> and the code crashes and restarts, there’s no additional logs or information on what the error is.</p>
<p>Our full robot code is <a href="https://github.com/FRC-Team3484/X25_RobotCode/tree/testing" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">here</a>, and the <code>GoToPose</code> function is inside <a href="https://github.com/FRC-Team3484/X25_RobotCode/blob/5997ec7f61f8652e48fab1120313432f7dffc014/src/main/cpp/subsystems/DrivetrainSubsystem.cpp#L258" rel="noopener nofollow ugc"><code>DrivetrainSubsystem.cpp</code></a>.</p>
<p>Any advice on how to fix this issue would be appreciated!</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-03-29T17:56:46.496Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":12,"reads":68,"readers_count":67,"score":88.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":497333,"topic_slug":"bad-optional-access-when-generating-paths-using-pathplanner","display_username":"nfoert","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/FRC-Team3484/X25_RobotCode/tree/testing","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - FRC-Team3484/X25_RobotCode at testing","clicks":1},{"url":"https://github.com/FRC-Team3484/X25_RobotCode/blob/5997ec7f61f8652e48fab1120313432f7dffc014/src/main/cpp/subsystems/DrivetrainSubsystem.cpp#L258","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"X25_RobotCode/src/main/cpp/subsystems/DrivetrainSubsystem.cpp at 5997ec7f61f8652e48fab1120313432f7dffc014 · FRC-Team3484/X25_RobotCode · GitHub","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":68675,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3484 | Head programmer and scout"},"post_url":"/t/bad-optional-access-when-generating-paths-using-pathplanner/497333/1","custom_user_title":"3484 | Head programmer and scout","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3572528,"name