<p>We were hoping to try PathPlanners’ path finding instead of the waypoints and see if the issue still showed up there, but haven’t had time yet.</p>
<p>Occasionally we were also getting an error that said something like <code>X and Y of Rotation2D component were zero</code> with the same crashing behavior, this may be related but I’m not sure</p>
<p>We did test the <code>Debug robot code</code> open in VSCode, but all it said when the error occurred that it was a crash in just in time compiled code, which didn’t help us at all</p>
<p>Considering you’re also having similar issues makes me wonder if it’s a bug in PathPlanner<br>
I do see <a href="https://github.com/mjansen4857/pathplanner/issues/1056" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">these</a>  <a href="https://github.com/mjansen4857/pathplanner/issues/984" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">two</a> issues that could be related (To the <code>x and y rotation component are zero</code> error at least). The most recent of which was fixed in <a href="https://github.com/mjansen4857/pathplanner/releases/tag/v2025.2.6" rel="noopener nofollow ugc"><code>v2025.2.6</code></a> of PathPlanner. Our robot code is currently running <code>v2025.2.5</code>, so perhaps updating could fix some of our issues</p>
